news.title: One-time settlement for property tax in Bengaluru till July 31: Karnataka deputy CM
news.para: The one-time settlement (OTS) scheme will end on July 31 and hence I urge people to make use of the opportunity to clear the outstanding payments," said Shivakumar.

news.title: China's Dexin ordered to liquidate by Hong Kong court
news.para: Dexin joined the growing ranks of Chinese developers under pressure from creditors in the aftermath of a years-long crisis in China's property market.

news.title: Shivraj Singh Chouhan is rural development minister, panchayati raj goes to Lalan Singh
news.para: The panchayati raj ministry, which was created first in 2004, looks after transferring grants to rural local bodies for civic programmes and their functioning.

news.title: CREDAI wants UP-RERA to reconsider order which made OC a must for possession letter
news.para: "The UP RERA needs to reconsider this decision in the benefit of homebuyers," said CREDAI western Uttar Pradesh Secretary Dinesh Gupta.

news.title: UK Consulate buys nearly 15,000 sq ft office in Mumbai's Lower Parel
news.para: The UK Consulate has acquired the office space spread across a total 12 units on the 19th floor of the tower from Lodha Group’s listed entity Macrotech Developers.

news.title: Union cabinet approves government assistance for constructing three crore PMAY houses
news.para: "It has been decided in the Cabinet meeting today to provide assistance to three crore additional rural and urban households for the construction of houses to meet the housing requirements arising out of the increase in the number of eligible families," officials said.

news.title: Manohar Lal Khattar appointed as new housing and urban affairs minister
news.para: The Union Housing and Urban Affairs Ministry is mandated to execute various projects including Modi government's flagship PM Awas Yojna, Swachh Bharat Mission (Urban) and the ambitious Central Vista redevelopment plan.

news.title: Sebi to auction 22 properties of seven companies in July 2024
news.para: ​Other firms, whose properties will also be auctioned, are Tower Infotech Group, Waris Group, Teachers' Welfare Credit and Holding Group, and Annex Infrastructure India Ltd.

news.title: Is the Indian real estate market a bubble? Uncovering the truth behind the hype
news.para: Prices may plateau or correct, but a major crash seems unlikely given the strong economic fundamentals and rising incomes. However, investors should still conduct due diligence and be cautious about speculative investments.

news.title: Lucknow civic body begins demolition of illegal constructions
news.para: For the past two days, we have been appealing to shift their belongings and move to their new apartment in Vasant Kunj. I personally went there and requested people. Most of them have shifted," Tripathi told PTI.

news.title: MahaRERA keeps registration of 1,750 lapsed housing projects in abeyance
news.para: The Maharashtra Real Estate Regulatory Authority (MahaRERA) has put the registration of 1,750 lapsed housing projects on hold across the state and plans to take similar action on 1,137 more projects.

news.title: Suraksha group to pay first instalment of Rs 133 crore to YEIDA before August 24
news.para: Suraksha Group, now controlling debt-ridden Jaypee Infratech, will pay ₹133 crore to Yamuna Expressway Industrial Development Authority (YEIDA) within three months as part of a ₹1,334 crore compensation to farmers.

news.title: Suspended board of Jaiprakash Associates moves NCLAT
news.para: The suspended board of Jaiprakash Associates has appealed to the NCLAT against the NCLT's order to initiate insolvency proceedings. ICICI Bank's insolvency plea was admitted in June, with Bhuvan Madan appointed as Interim Resolution Professional.

news.title: Haryana government to give 100 sq yards plots to over 7,500 BPL families
news.para: Besides the distribution of these certificates, the registration of the respective plots will also be done on the spot, he said. Saini said the beneficiaries will be given possession certificates of the plots at many places in Haryana on Monday.

news.title: FONRWA demands regularisation of unauthorised construction in Noida
news.para: ​According to the RWA federation, which has over 200 member RWAs in the city, this will address the issues of a lack of low-cost housing for middle and lower-middle-class citizens.

news.title: Total environment repays Rs 2,070 crore dues to top lenders
news.para: The fund was secured from leading banks like State Bank of India, Standard Chartered Bank, ICICI Bank, Axis Bank and RBL Bank at interest rates ranging from 9.7% to 12.5%.

news.title: Gurugram: FIR filed against IREO Group, Oberoi Realty MDs for alleged fraud
news.para: ​The FIR was filed on the orders of the Chief Judicial Magistrate at the DLF phase 2 police station on Friday following a complaint lodged by Advance India Projects Limited (AIPL), citing allegations of cheating, criminal breach of trust and forgery against the accused, the police said.

news.title: UP-RERA sets model format for possession letters to protect allottees
news.para: Sanjay Bhoosreddy, chairman, UP-RERA said, "Offer of possession should be meant only for the purpose of taking possession. Hence, we have made available a model offer of possession on the portal and any other format of letter will not be valid."

news.title: Mumbai: Chembur society repays Rs 20 crore loan six months after OC
news.para: Chitra is one among several societies in Mumbai which did not reach out to private builders and instead opted to redevelop their buildings themselves by appointing consultants, architects and contractors.

news.title: Greater Noida authority cracks down on illegal construction to reclaim land worth Rs 150 crore
news.para: On Saturday morning, a team from Work Circle Three demolished ongoing illegal constructions on plots numbered 517, 964, 981, 985, 995 and 1,007 in Tusyana village," the statement said.
